# Run Medusa inside this pnpm monorepo.
#
# Two resolution quirks need help under pnpm's strict isolated layout:
#  1. Medusa's plugin loader require()s plugin packages (e.g.
#     "medusa-plugin-zatca/.medusa/server/src/modules/zatca") from inside
#     @medusajs/* framework code, so the suite's workspace packages must be
#     visible on the framework's resolution path.
#  2. Medusa's admin bundler auto-imports an admin extension from every
#     installed @medusajs/* module (e.g. "@medusajs/draft-order/admin") and
#     expects @medusajs/*, react, and react-dom in a flat node_modules.
#
# Source-level boundaries are still enforced by dependency-cruiser, which reads
# package.json — not node_modules layout — so the published packages keep
# their strict dependency contracts.
hoist-workspace-packages=true
public-hoist-pattern[]=@medusajs/*
public-hoist-pattern[]=@medusa-ksa/*
public-hoist-pattern[]=medusa-payment-*
public-hoist-pattern[]=medusa-fulfillment-*
public-hoist-pattern[]=medusa-notification-*
public-hoist-pattern[]=medusa-plugin-*
public-hoist-pattern[]=react
public-hoist-pattern[]=react-dom
